      .span10
        img#backupimg(src="/images/MaconTiltShadow.png")
        .row-fluid
          .span12
            .well#eventpiece
              h1(style='font-size:30pt;') Macon Maps
              br
              h3 Open Data for Middle Georgia
              br
              h3 Brought to you by&nbsp;
                a(href="http://codeforamerica.org") Code for America
              br
              div(style="clear:both;")

        .row-fluid
          .span6
            h2 About OpenStreetMap
            p
              h4 Code for America is opening data to make the best map of Macon, ever.
            p
              span When you edit&nbsp;
              a(href='http://www.openstreetmap.org/?lat=32.845&lon=-83.6348&zoom=14&layers=Q') OpenStreetMap
              span &nbsp;you're making a better map for all of us.
            p How do companies catch up to Google and release their own maps?&nbsp;
              a(href="http://arstechnica.com/apple/2012/05/two-months-later-apple-acknowledges-use-of-openstreetmap-in-iphoto/") They use OpenStreetMap.
            p Craigslist is&nbsp;
              a(href="http://idealab.talkingpointsmemo.com/2012/08/craigslist-maps-test-openstreetmap.php") mapping your next apartment
              span &nbsp;on OpenStreetMap.
            p Foursquare uses and edits OpenStreetMap&nbsp;
              a(href="http://foursquare.com") to map places and check-ins worldwide
            p OpenStreetMap is even used to make&nbsp;
              a(href="http://softcities.net/") blankets and "mapkins".
     
          .span6
            h2 Build on it
            p Add this OpenStreetMap layer on top of
            ul.span5.nav.nav-list
              li.active Google Maps
              li Esri JS
              li Leaflet
              li OpenLayers
              li Bing Maps
              li MapBox
            div.span6.well
              span map = new google.maps.Map(document.getElementById("map"), { mapTypeControlOptions:{ mapTypeIds:[google.maps.MapTypeId.ROADMAP, google.maps.MapTypeId.SATELLITE, 'MapQuest'] } });
              br
              span osmLayer = new google.maps.ImageMapType({
              br
              span &nbsp;&nbsp;getTileUrl: function(coord, zoom){
              br
              span &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;return "http://otile1.mqcdn.com/tiles/1.0.0/osm/" + zoom + "/" + coord.x + "/" + coord.y + ".jpg";
              br
              span &nbsp;&nbsp;},
              br
              span &nbsp;&nbsp;tileSize: new google.maps.Size(256, 256),
              br
              span &nbsp;&nbsp;isPng: false,
              br
              span &nbsp;&nbsp;alt: "OpenStreetMap",
              br
              span &nbsp;&nbsp;name: "OpenStreetMap",
              br
              span &nbsp;&nbsp;maxZoom: 19
              br
              span });
              br
              span map.mapTypes.set('OpenStreetMap', osmLayer);


        .row-fluid
          .span6
            h2 Data Tips
            ul
              li You can view almost any KML file in Google Maps. Paste the URL into the search bar.
              li
                span You can download Macon and Bibb County data from OpenStreetMap at&nbsp;
                a(href="http://metro.teczno.com/") metro.teczno.com
              li When building on top of OpenStreetMap, always give credit. The data is free, but the contributors have rights.

